verbose_text: Inclusion criteria included age 12-30 years, clinical diagnosis of type 1 diabetes of at least 1 year 's duration, current use of insulin pump therapy, A1C < 9% (< 75 mmol / mol), BMI < 95th percentile for age and sex, normal hematocrit and serum creatinine levels, no other chronic medical condition (except treated hypothyroidism), and no medications (other than insulin) known to affect blood glucose levels; also, female subjects could not be pregnant or lactating.
